    "description": "Su-Kam Power Systems Asia Pacific Associates is actively seeking a talented and motivated Manufacturing Engineer to join our dynamic team in Ghaziabad. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Su-Kam Power Systems Asia Pacific Associates:\nSu-Kam Power Systems Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Coordinate with logistics for dispatching finished goods\n• Maintain accurate production records and prepare daily reports\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Quality Control\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in ISO 9001\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in APQP\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Ghaziabad, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Su-Kam Power Systems Asia Pacific Associates!",
